str_is_iso:
/-- The structure map of the inital algebra is an isomorphism,
hence endofunctors preserve their initial algebras
-/
theorem str_is_iso (h : Limits.IsInitial A) : IsIso A.str :=
  { out := ⟨str_inv h, right_inv _, left_inv _⟩ }
#align str_is_iso str_is_iso
right_inv:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr𝟙» -/
theorem right_inv : «expr ≫ » A.str (str_inv h) = («expr𝟙») _ :=
  by
  rw [str_inv, ← (h.to ⟨F.obj A.1, F.map A.str⟩).h, ← F.map_id, ← F.map_comp]
  congr
  exact left_inv h
#align right_inv right_inv
mono_of_mono:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/-- An algebra morphism with an underlying monomorphism hom in `C` is an algebra monomorphism. -/
theorem mono_of_mono {X Y : coalgebra F} (f : «expr ⟶ » X Y) [h : Mono f.1] : Mono f :=
  (forget F).mono_of_mono_map h
#align mono_of_mono mono_of_mono
left_inv':
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr𝟙» -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr𝟙» -/
theorem left_inv' : (⟨«expr ≫ » (str_inv h) A.str⟩ : «expr ⟶ » A A) = («expr𝟙») A :=
  Limits.IsInitial.hom_ext h _ ((«expr𝟙») A)
#align left_inv' left_inv'
left_inv:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr𝟙» -/
theorem left_inv : «expr ≫ » (str_inv h) A.str = («expr𝟙») _ :=
  congr_arg hom.f (left_inv' h)
#align left_inv left_inv
iso_of_iso:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/-- A coalgebra morphism with an underlying isomorphism hom in `C` is a coalgebra isomorphism. -/
theorem iso_of_iso (f : «expr ⟶ » V₀ V₁) [IsIso f.1] : IsIso f :=
  ⟨⟨{   f := inv f.1
        h' := by
          rw [is_iso.eq_inv_comp f.1, ← category.assoc, ← f.h, category.assoc]
          simp },
      by tidy⟩⟩
#align iso_of_iso iso_of_iso

hom_equiv_naturality_str_symm:

/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
theorem coalgebra.hom_equiv_naturality_str_symm (adj : «expr ⊣ » F G) (V₁ V₂ : coalgebra G) (f : «expr ⟶ » V₁ V₂) :
    «expr ≫ » (F.map f.f) ((adj.hom_equiv V₂.V V₂.V).symm V₂.str) =
      «expr ≫ » ((adj.hom_equiv V₁.V V₁.V).symm V₁.str) f.f :=
  by rw [← adjunction.hom_equiv_naturality_left_symm, ← adjunction.hom_equiv_naturality_right_symm, f.h]
